ef>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/bollywood-iifa-2018-here-is-the-complete-list-of-winners-449203|title=International Indian Film Academy Awards (IIFA 2018): Here's the complete list of winners|last=Shrivastava|first=Anuradha|date=25 June 2018|website=indiatvnews.com|access-date=9 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Nominations==\n2016\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Music Director]] for [[Kapoor & Sons]] along with [[Amaal Mallik]], [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]], [[Arko Pravo Mukherjee]], [[Benny Dayal]], [[Nucleya]]\n2017\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Music Director]] for [[Badrinath Ki Dulhania]] along with [[Amaal Mallik]] & [[Akhil Sachdeva]]\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Music Director]] for [[Half Girlfriend (film)|Half Girlfriend]] along with [[Mithoon]], [[Farhan Saeed]], [[Rishi Rich]], [[Ami Mishra]], [[Rahul Mishra]]\n* [[Filmfare Award for Best Music Director]] for [[Bareilly Ki Barfi]] along with [[Arko Pravo Mukherjee]], [[Samira Koppikar]], Sameer Uddin & Vayu\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|id=7565692|name=Tanishk Bagchi}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bagchi, Tanishk}}\n[[Category:Indian film score composers]]\n[[Category:Indian male composers]]\n[[Category:Jingle composers]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male film score composers]]\n[[Category:Scottish Church College, Calcutta alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Calcutta alumni]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n\n\n{{India-composer-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian music producer, composer, lyricist and singer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2019}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Tanishk Bagchi\n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = \n| landscape        = \n| caption          = Tanishk Bagchi\n| birth_date       = 22 November<ref>{{cite tweet |user=tanishkbagchi |author=Tanishk Bagchi |number=1065682816757723136 |date=22 November 2018 |title=We share music & birthday! Happy Birthday @EricnPillai \ud83c\udf82\ud83c\udf7e |accessdate=3 May 2019}}</ref>\n| genre            = {{flatlist|\n* [[Film soundtrack]]\n* [[Music of Bollywood]]\n* [[Pop music|pop]]\n}}\n| occupation       = {{hlist|Music producer|composer|arranger|singer|lyricist}}\n| years_active     = <!-- {{start date|2014}}\u2013 (or \u2013present) --> 2012\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[T-Series (company)|T-Series]]\n* [[Zee Music Company]]\n* [[Sony Music India]]\n* [[Saregama]]\n* [[Tips Industries|Tips]]\n}}\n| associated_acts  = {{flatlist|\n* [[A.R. Rahman]]\n* [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]]\n* [[Amit Mishra (singer)|Amit Mishra]]\n* [[Neha Kakkar]]\n* [[Dhvani Bhanushali]]\n* [[Kshmr]]\n* [[Dillon Francis]]\n* [[Chantel Jeffries]]\n}}\n| website          = \n| module           = \n| module2          = \n| module3          = \n| relatives        = \n}}\n'''Tanishk Bagchi''' (born 22 November) is an Indian music producer, composer, singer and lyricist.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2018/dec/25/i-dont-remix-i-recreate-says-tanishk-baghchi-1916144.html|title=I don't remix, I recreate: Tanishk Bagchi on composing for 'Simmba'|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=26 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and background ==\nHailing from [[Kolkata]], Bagchi was born to musicians Nandakumar Bagchi and Sharmistha Das. He attended [[The Frank Anthony Public School, Kolkata|Frank Anthony Public School]] and [[Scottish Church Collegiate School|Scottish Church Collegiate School, Kolkata]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/entertainment/humma-humma-to-tamma-tamma-mdash-he-rsquo-s-bolly-rsquo-s-music-man-of-the-moment-meet-calcutta-boy-tanishk-bagchi/cid/1426727|title=Humma Humma to Tamma Tamma \u2013 he's Bolly's music man of the moment. Meet Calcutta boy Tanishk Bagchi|website=The Telegraph|location=Kolkota|access-date=9 July 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nHe made his debut in Bollywood with the song \"Banno\" composed with Vayu Srivastava from the film ''[[Tanu Weds Manu Returns]]'' in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-i-want-older-melodies-to-come-back-says-tanishk-bagchi-2595100|title=I want older melodies to come back, says Tanishk Bagchi|date=19 March 2018|website=dna|access-date=2 January 2019}}</ref> Before composing for films, he produced and arranged music for TV shows.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/remo-is-right-in-criticising-humma-humma-remake-composer-tanishk/story-CBRA9QkRtHBpGznLbM.html|title=Remo is right in criticising Humma Humma:composer Tanishk|author=Samarth Goyal|date=6 February 2017|work=[[Hindustan Times]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/tanishk-bagchi-tanu-weds-manu-returns-kangana-ranaut-r-madhavan/1/439820.html|title=Tanishk Narula is set for big (screen) league|author=Vinayak Chakravorty|date=23 May 2015|work=[[India Today]]|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref> Since then, he has composed several hit songs including the ''[[Badrinath Ki Dulhania]]'' title track.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/Music-is-beyond-politics-says-Tanishk-Bagchi/articleshow/52448435.cms|title=Music is beyond politics, says Tanishk Bagchi|author=V Lakshmi|date=17 January 2017|work=[[The Times of India]]|accessdate=6 February 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radioandmusic.com/entertainment/editorial/news/160227-i-was-waiting-song-kapoor-sons-bolna-tanishk|title=I was waiting for a song like Kapoor & Sons' 'Bolna': Tanishk Narula|date=27 February 2016|work=RadioandMusic.com}}</ref> He won the 2018 [[IIFA Award for Best Music Director]] for the film [[Badrinath Ki Dulhania]]. He recently won the [[Zee Cine Award]] for Song of the Year for his song Baarish. Later he released his single \"Khud Se Zyada\" with the independent record label Vyrl originals as a singer-songwriter.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tanishk Bagchi and Zara Khan's debut single, Khudse Zyada, releases today - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/music/news/tanishk-bagchi-and-zara-khans-debut-single-khudse-zyada-releases-today/articleshow/70752102.cms |website=The Times of India |last=Sen |first=Debarati S. |date=21 August 2019 |accessdate=21 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|- style=\"background:#cfc; text-align:center;\"\n| '''Year'''\n| '''Film'''\n| '''Track(s)'''\n| '''Singer(s)'''\n| '''Writer(s)'''\n| '''Notes''' \n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"|2015\n| ''[[Tanu Weds Manu Returns]]''\n| \"Banno\"\n|[[Brijesh Shandilya]], Swati Sharma\n|Vayu \n|Along with Vayu\n|-\n| ''[[Kis Kisko Pyaar Karoon]]''\n| \"Samandar\"\n|[[Jubin Nautiyal]], [[Shreya Ghoshal]]\n|Arafat Mehmood\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|2016\n| ''[[Kapoor & Sons]]''\n| \"[[Bolna (song)|Bolna]]\"\n|[[Arijit Singh]], [[Asees Kaur]]\n|Dr. Devendra Kafir\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Sarbjit (film)|Sarbjit]]''\n| \"Rabba\"\n|[[Shafqat Amanat Ali]]\n|Arafat Mehmood\n|\n|-\n|\"Allah Hu Allah\"\n|[[Shashaa Tirupati]], Altamash Faridi, Rabbani Mustafa Khan\n|Haider Najmi\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Housefull 3]]''\n| \"Fake Ishq\"\n|[[Kailash Kher]]\n|Arafat Mehmood, [[Sajid-Farhad]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"29\" |2017\n| ''[[Ok Jaanu]]''\n| \"[[Humma Humma|The Humma Song]] (Remake)\"\n|Jubin Nautiyal, Shashaa Tirupati, Badshah, Tanishk Bagchi \n|[[Mehboob (lyricist)|Mehboob]], Badshah \n|Along with [[Badshah (rapper)|Badshah]]\n|-\n| ''[[Noor (film)|Noor]]''\n| \"Gulabi Retro Mix (Remake)\"\n|[[Sonu Nigam]]\n|\n|\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Badrinath Ki Dulhania]]''\n| \"Badri Ki Dulhania (Title Track)\"\n|[[Dev Negi]], [[Neha Kakkar]], [[Monali Thakur]], [[Ikka Singh]]\n|[[Shabbir Ahmed (lyricist)|Shabbir Ahmed]]\n|\n|-\n|\"Tamma Tamma Again (Remake)\"\n|[[Bappi Lahiri]], [[Anuradha Paudwal]], Badshah \n|[[Indeevar]], Badshah \n|\n|-\n|rowspa